Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the 24th Annual TAPS National Military Survivor celebration in Arlington, Virginia. He expressed gratitude and respect to the Gold Star Families, honoring their loved ones who have served and made the ultimate sacrifice for the United States. Pence assured the families that their loved ones' names and service will always be remembered, and that Americans across the country will pause and remember them on Memorial Day. He also commended the mentors who provide support and comfort to the families, and emphasized the importance of finding community and encouragement at the Good Grief Camp. Pence concluded by expressing his faith in America's future and the strength of the families in attendance.